manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: This bookshelf has four and five tiers different specifications. If you want to add additional storage space, you can choose more than 2 products to combine. Simple design, its retro fashion style makes the whole shelf more ornamental, which can be used to decorate your home or office. The structure is firm, and the ladder rack that can be used for a long time is made of precise technology and high-quality materials, which ensures the stability and safety of the bookcase.

It can be used as a storage rack for toiletries, towels, sundries, ornaments, books, plants, spices and small household appliances. You can also delete a tier to meet your special storage needs. No matter which room it is placed in, it can fully play its role. We also added four hooks for the product to facilitate hanging some small items.

Anti-tip accessory and S-hooks You can firmly fix the bookshelf to the wall with the safety straps and screws provided in the package. Use the 4 S shaped hooks on the side of the storage rack for hanging utensils, headphone,plant and more. X-shaped reinforcement frame X-frame provides additional stability, durability, and safety to withstand everyday use in your home for years. water-proof panel Using high-quality MDF board, the surface is smooth, waterproof, scratch-resistant and easy to clean, just wipe it with a damp cloth. Retro brown is more suitable for your home. 360° adjustable feet Equipped with 4 height-adjustable feet for consistent height on uneven floors without scratching your floor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Thin, spindly, wobbly legs in too many pieces
reviews.reviewText: The legs on this bookcase are thin, spindly and wobbly (only 9/16" wide). The legs come in 3 pieces each which adds to the wobbliness and makes it look chintzy. This is why it needs a back brace and why It also comes with straps to anchor it to a wall. Legs on something this tall should be solid or at the most only 2 sections. My other pieces of furniture like this (black iron with fake wooden shelves) have at least 3/4" to 1"+ wide legs and are in one piece which makes them much more stable and attractive. I'm sure they're like this because it makes shipping easier/cheaper (the leg pieces are basically the same length as the shelves) which I understand for the price, but then a price is paid. I'm keeping it only because I needed this size, and it won't be a centerpiece.
